    <div class="main review-item" id="1008653">
        

  <header class="main-hd">
    <h3 class="title">
      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/1008653/" class="title-link">自由，不要逃避</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-1008653"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/min/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u1017955-16.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/min/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">薄荷and薄荷</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar50 main-title-rating" title="力荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2005-10-27"
      class="main-meta">2005-10-27 20:18:56</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_1008653_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                  这本书主要是从欧洲历史着眼。人在文艺复兴以前的社会中（主要是指中世纪）缺乏自由，但却处在稳定的社会结构中。社会虽然严格的规定了每个人的社会身分和地位，不许越雷池半步，但同时也给余个人以保障和安全感，使人不用为自己的前途、命运担心。（参考封建时代或改革开放前...

                    <a class="pl" href="https://book.douban.com/review/1008653/#comments">(32回应)</a>
                  <div class="more-info pl clearfix">
                    <span class="left">196有用 / 14没用</span>
                  </div>
            </div>
